name: South Korea
summary: South Korea's parliament has overturned President Yoon Suk-yeol's declaration of martial law, defying his authority. The move follows protests outside parliament against the declaration. The president had imposed martial law to control the protests, but the parliament voted to lift it, sending a strong message of opposition. The situation remains tense, with demonstrations continuing and the government facing criticism for its handling of the situation.
